definitions.definition: (countable) A patronymic surname, from Welsh common in Wales, derived from the given name Evan (or Ifan in Welsh).
A number of places in the United States:
definitions.example: A city (home rule municipality) in Weld County, Colorado.

definitions.definition: A city (home rule municipality) in Weld County, Colorado.
A census-designated place in Columbia County, Georgia.
A town in Erie County, New York.
An unincorporated  community in Jackson County, West Virginia.
